Of the 21 members:
11 shall be practicing licensed physicians, at least one of whom shall be a doctor of osteopathy, appointed as provided in subsections (d) and (e) of this section;
1 shall be a practicing licensed physician appointed at the Governor's discretion;
1 shall be a representative of the Department nominated by the Secretary;
1 shall be a certified physician assistant appointed at the Governor's discretion as provided in subsections (f) and (g) of this section;
1 shall be a practicing licensed physician with a full-time faculty appointment appointed to serve as a representative of an academic medical institution in this State appointed from a list containing:
5 shall be consumer members; and
1 shall be a public member knowledgeable in risk management or quality assurance matters appointed from a list submitted by the Maryland Hospital Association.

Each consumer or public member of the Board:
Shall be a member of the general public;
Shall be a resident of the State for at least 5 years;
May not be or ever have been a physician or in training to become a physician;
May not have a household member who is a physician or in training to become a physician;
May not have a household member who participates in a commercial or professional field related to medicine; and
May not have had within 2 years before appointment a substantial financial interest in a person regulated by the Board.

For each vacancy of a practicing licensed physician appointed in accordance with subsection (a)(2)(i) of this section, the Board shall:
Notify all practicing licensed physicians and professional organizations representing at least 25 licensed physicians in the State of the vacancy;
Provide information regarding the selection process as provided under subsection (a)(2)(i) of this section;
Solicit nominations for the vacancy; and
Forward to the Governor:

For the vacancy of a certified physician assistant appointed in accordance with subsection (a)(2)(iv) of this section, the Board shall:
Notify all practicing certified physician assistants and professional organizations representing at least 25 certified physician assistants in the State of the vacancy;
Provide information regarding the selection process as provided under subsection (a)(2)(iv) of this section;
Solicit nominations for the vacancy; and
Forward to the Governor:
